        "concerns": [
          "We noticed that 2.5 treatments running past closing time daily at Monterey represents a meaningful gap\u2014this metric carries operational and cultural weight that warrants attention. While Scheduler Compliance and Avg Delay both track at company benchmarks, the frequency of late-running treatments suggests that either schedule buffers may need calibration, patient arrivals may be clustering toward day-end, or unexpected procedure durations are elongating the day. A brief data review focused on which appointment slots most often overrun and whether iOptimize recommendations are being applied uniformly across all time slots could surface quick wins."
        ],
        "recommendations": [
